1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:26,040
I didn't come back
because I wanted Dad's stupid inheritance.

2
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:28,360
<i>So I need some men to handle him.</i>

3
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:29,920
<i>Ten percent of the inheritance</i>

4
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,960
<i>will be transferred</i>
<i>to your account immediately.</i>

5
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:33,400
And I'll also let you have someone.

6
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:35,120
We meet again.

7
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:36,680
It's clearly fate.

8
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:39,600
<i>May you and her be together</i>
<i>in the same grave</i>

9
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:41,960
until the end of time, Mr. Chalit.

10
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:43,440
I'll be waiting for you, Mr. Yai.

11
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:11,000
Hey, Dad. This is our home.

12
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:13,480
Aren't we going back to Paisal Farm?

13
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,720
Yeah.

14
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:19,600
Pan. If you want to know,
just go ask Mr. Yai.

15
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:24,080
Maybe the drug's effect
hasn't worn off yet.

16
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:25,760
Drug?

17
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:27,720
What drug?

18
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:31,120
Don't tell me you drugged Pin
when we stopped at the gas station!

19
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:35,880
Ugh, Yai.

20
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:40,680
Oh, Mr. Yai.

21
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:43,840
- Aunt Pen, is the guest room ready?
- Yes, it's ready to use.

22
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:46,480
The bed is made, just as you requested.

23
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:48,600
But why are you in such a hurry?

24
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:51,640
Oh, oh. Pload, wait.

25
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:55,920
That girl Mr. Yai is carrying, who is she?

26
00:04:57,760 --> 00:05:00,600
She's the daughter
of a maid at Paisal Farm.

27
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:02,920
- Pen.
- Huh?

28
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Don't ask any more questions.

29
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:07,800
Mr. Yai will explain everything to you.

30
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:11,320
Just do everything and say everything
Mr. Yai asks you to, alright?

31
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:17,320
Pan, wait.

32
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,080
What's the hurry?

33
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:21,120
Who's the girl Mr. Yai was carrying?

34
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,040
Tell me.

35
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,840
Please don't ask me, Aunt Pen.

36
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,560
I need to keep it zipped for now.

37
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,360
What is going on?

38
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:32,680
You couldn't just tell me?

39
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:37,560
Oh, Madam. Madam.

40
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:40,280
Pin hasn't come home.

41
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,920
Noi said she was out bringing you a bag.

42
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,080
Is that true?

43
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,480
Yes.

44
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:48,400
But I didn't ask where she'd go next.

45
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:49,960
Let's report her as missing, Aunt Un.

46
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,680
Don't do that!

47
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:59,320
Why not, Madam?

48
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:03,880
I know you'll be upset if I tell you.

49
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:07,600
But if I don't, I'll feel sorry for you.

50
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,720
Madam.

51
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:13,720
Please tell me.

52
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:15,920
What happened to Pin?

53
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:20,480
Well, after Pin gave me the bag,

54
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:23,240
Yai drove over and picked her up.

55
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:25,600
Teera saw it with his own eyes.

56
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,240
Right, Teera?

57
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:28,880
Yes.

58
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,680
Aunt Un! Aunt Un!

59
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:46,640
Mr. Yai.

60
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:49,720
You want the madam

61
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:52,600
to think you and Pinanong got killed?

62
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:57,680
Yes, Uncle.

63
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,800
And what does that achieve?

64
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:03,400
Satisfaction, Dad.

65
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:05,760
Happiness from tricking people.

66
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:08,280
Hey, Pan.

67
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:11,120
Pan is partly right.

68
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:13,720
I want to teach those people a lesson.

69
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:16,120
But I think it's too risky.

70
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:21,760
If you slip up just like I once did…

71
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,040
I don't want it to happen to you too.

72
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:35,040
<i>I once saw Madam meeting a man,</i>

73
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:38,240
<i>but I had no evidence.</i>

74
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:42,120
<i>So I waited for the right moment</i>
<i>to catch him in the act.</i>

75
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:55,280
Hey. Don't try to escape.

76
00:07:58,840 --> 00:08:02,040
That man who climbed up into your room,

77
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:04,480
where is he, Madam?

78
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,880
You've underestimated me, idiot.

79
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:12,800
- Help! Help!
- Huh?

80
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:14,120
- Get off me! Get off!
- Let go.

81
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,680
- Don't do anything to me!
- Let go.

82
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:17,200
He's harassing me! Help!

83
00:08:17,280 --> 00:08:18,760
- Let go.
- Pload!

84
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:21,280
Mr. Paisal.

85
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:28,200
He broke into my room
and tried to force himself on me…

86
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,480
She's lying.

87
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:33,960
I caught her with another man in her room.

88
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:35,320
But he ran away.

89
00:08:36,679 --> 00:08:38,200
She had a husband before.

90
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:40,039
She lied to you, sir.

91
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:45,760
That's not true… Punish him for me.

92
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:47,960
- Pload!
- Mr. Paisal.

93
00:08:56,680 --> 00:09:00,400
<i>I fell into her trap</i>
<i>and had to retreat here.</i>

94
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:03,080
<i>But I didn't expect them</i>

95
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:06,360
<i>to frame you as a murderer.</i>

96
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:34,040
Hey. Give me that.

97
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:41,800
You think you're tough, huh?

98
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:45,240
Hey, stop. Come here.

99
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:53,520
Get lost, all of you.

100
00:09:59,680 --> 00:10:00,760
Are you okay?

101
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:03,000
I'm sorry I'm late.

102
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:13,760
I admit I was a bit careless this time,

103
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:18,080
but I promise
to be more careful next time.

104
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:21,280
So, you're going to let Tong
get away with it?

105
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:24,520
You think that he won't come for you?

106
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:28,000
Hey, they might not
be afraid of the police.

107
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:31,480
But he probably doesn't want to get
into trouble with Bandit Pload's gang.

108
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,400
Pin, you're awake?

109
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:02,280
Uh…

110
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:06,360
Where are we?

111
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:13,360
This is a thieves' den.

112
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:17,160
I forgot to formally introduce the boss.

113
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,400
This is Bandit Pload,

114
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:22,880
the legendary cutthroat master thief.

115
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:26,840
Pload?

116
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:39,680
Hey, Phong.

117
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:42,840
Yes, Boss?

118
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,600
Are the explosives

119
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:47,760
I told you to prepare ready?

120
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:56,440
The hand grenades, shrapnel bombs,
and machine guns are all ready, Dad.

121
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:58,200
Just waiting for the order to attack.

122
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,440
Good.

123
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:02,960
Gather everyone here.

124
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:04,760
Follow the original plan.

125
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:10,440
We're going to raid the whole village.

126
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:14,400
Anyone who resists will be killed

127
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:16,640
without mercy.

128
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:18,840
Let's go.

129
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:20,240
Let's go.

130
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:24,440
Well?

131
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:26,440
The master thief has gone.

132
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:28,560
Isn't the lesser thief going to follow?

133
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:32,120
I have to keep an eye on the hostage.

134
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:36,640
I'm thinking of a ransom,
a million or two.

135
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:48,360
Is this place really a thieves' lair?

136
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:52,520
Do you think bandits
only lived in caves in the forest?

137
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,640
We're modern-day bandits, girl.

138
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:01,560
Oh, this is Aunt Pen, Bandit Pload's wife.

139
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:09,880
Pin. Are you hungry?

140
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:12,320
Uh… Not really.

141
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,040
What?

142
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:17,320
I was just asking.

143
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:19,680
What's wrong with her?
Why did she have to run from me?

144
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:21,080
That's why, Aunt Pen.

145
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:24,800
A knife? Oh, it scared me too.

146
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:26,880
I was peeling bitter beans.

147
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:48,800
If you don't wanna end up like that phone,

148
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:50,520
don't try to contact anyone.

149
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:53,680
Why aren't you taking me back to the farm?

150
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:56,280
Madam Krongsuk tricked you
into meeting with Mr. Tong

151
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:57,640
and planned to have him kill us.

152
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:59,000
Just know that.

153
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:02,600
Let me go back
to find out the truth myself.

154
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:04,920
I can't just listen
to your side of the story,

155
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,760
since you despise Madam.

156
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:08,880
Fine, I accused her.

157
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:11,120
If I see her, I'll shoot her on the spot.

158
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:15,720
If you still don't want to go back,
can you let me go back on my own?

159
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:19,600
Mom must be very worried
that I've disappeared.

160
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:20,640
No.

161
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:26,320
Then, can I just call my mom
and tell her I'm safe?

162
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:29,840
I'm afraid she'll fall ill again.

163
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:31,480
Please.

164
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:34,520
Please.

165
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:42,560
Can you please take it
to the doctor, Mr. Yai?

166
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:45,720
Don't try to befriend me. Get out of here.

167
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:49,720
If you don't help it,

168
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:52,800
it'll die for sure.

169
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:54,400
Please…

170
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:00,480
Please.

171
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:04,920
I'm so tired of you. I'll think about it.

172
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:11,800
Same old trick as always.

173
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:13,360
Do you think I'll give in?

174
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:22,960
- Let go! Let go of me!
- Ow, it hurts, Auntie!

175
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:24,120
Then let me go!

176
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:26,200
I'm going to drag Pin back home.

177
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:33,600
And where are you going to find her?

178
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:36,200
See? You'd barely make it to the entrance.

179
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:41,240
How was it, Jom?

180
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:43,000
Did you hear anything about Pin?

181
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,120
Nothing at all, Aunt Un.

182
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:49,000
But I've filed the police report.

183
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:52,520
If Pin hasn't returned in two days,
we'll go report another report.

184
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,440
Forget about her!

185
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:56,480
Don't bother trying to find her anymore!

186
00:15:56,560 --> 00:15:58,160
You ungrateful daughter.

187
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:02,320
She must have run away with Mr. Yai,
just like Madam said.

188
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:04,640
That can't be true, Auntie.

189
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:07,240
Mr. Yai was the one flirting with Pin.

190
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:08,800
He's the one who took her away.

191
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:11,160
True. And Madam was exaggerating.

192
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:12,840
Who knows if she made things up?

193
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:15,760
Don't you dare accuse Madam!

194
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:17,080
If you're going to blame someone,
blame me.

195
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:18,800
I didn't raise her well!

196
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:21,160
What a shame!

197
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:29,440
I bet my life

198
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:33,040
that Pin would never abandon you.

199
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:39,040
Also, Pin has been waiting
for the day Mr. Tatsana returns.

200
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:45,600
She will come back
to see Mr. Na. Believe me.

201
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:06,760
Noi!

202
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:09,440
- Yes?
- What are you doing?

203
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:14,280
Oh, Madam told me to burn
Mr. Yai and Mr. Pan's belongings.

204
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:15,839
Why are we burning them?

205
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:19,359
She said those two are never coming back.

206
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:25,720
Wait. Don't do it yet.

207
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,280
Which box is Pan's?

208
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:52,800
Mr. Na's returning to Thailand today.

209
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:57,280
So that's it.

210
00:17:58,280 --> 00:18:02,360
I thought you were genuinely worried
about Aunt Un and brought you a phone.

211
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:07,200
But if you just want to go see Na,
I don't think you need it.

212
00:18:08,280 --> 00:18:10,560
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai.

213
00:18:10,640 --> 00:18:12,200
Please let me use the phone.

214
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:14,840
I really want to call Mom.

215
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:16,560
Please.

216
00:18:16,640 --> 00:18:18,960
Take your hands off me,
and don't touch me again.

217
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:20,240
Back off.

218
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:22,840
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai.

219
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:26,480
Mr. Yai. Please!

220
00:18:26,560 --> 00:18:28,720
I'm really worried about my mom.

221
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:30,560
Mr. Yai.

222
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:53,000
Mr. Yai, please trust…

223
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:55,080
Auntie.

224
00:18:56,560 --> 00:18:58,200
I brought you a change of clothes.

225
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,840
Take a shower, and change into these.

226
00:19:00,920 --> 00:19:02,640
Then come eat with us downstairs, okay?

227
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:07,440
- Here.
- Thank you.

228
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:37,160
PRINCE OF SONGKLA UNIVERSITY

229
00:20:37,240 --> 00:20:38,880
MR. CHALIT THAMRONGRAT

230
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:46,000
BACHELOR OF ENGINEERING

231
00:20:50,280 --> 00:20:51,920
Oh, my. Pin.

232
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:54,520
You shouldn't have come in here.

233
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:57,440
If Mr. Yai sees you,
you're dead, you know?

234
00:20:57,520 --> 00:20:58,880
Come here.

235
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:10,440
Your meal's ready, Pin.

236
00:21:10,520 --> 00:21:11,800
Here.

237
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:15,880
Freshly cooked and still hot.

238
00:21:16,640 --> 00:21:18,440
Do you like southern curry?

239
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:20,240
I just made it fresh for you.

240
00:21:20,320 --> 00:21:22,320
Not too spicy. It's delicious.

241
00:21:24,320 --> 00:21:27,240
Aunt Pen, I'm really sorry.

242
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:29,840
I didn't mean to go into that room.

243
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:34,400
You don't need to apologize
or explain anything to me.

244
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:37,880
If I don't say anything,
Mr. Yai won't know.

245
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:42,800
So, does he really have
an engineering degree?

246
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:46,200
Ugh, if you keep asking questions,

247
00:21:46,280 --> 00:21:47,680
Mr. Yai will lock you up again.

248
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:48,600
Come eat.

249
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:52,040
Come on, dig in. Here.

250
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:57,800
Auntie.

251
00:21:57,880 --> 00:22:01,200
Why don't you convince Uncle Pload
to give up being a thief?

252
00:22:01,280 --> 00:22:04,000
Killing someone is a sin,
and you'll have to hide from the police,

253
00:22:04,080 --> 00:22:06,080
never knowing when you'll be caught.

254
00:22:10,280 --> 00:22:12,640
And Mr. Yai even has a degree.

255
00:22:12,720 --> 00:22:14,520
Why doesn't he find a good job?

256
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:18,880
I finished my water.

257
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:21,520
I'll go get some more.

258
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:23,360
Oh, I'll bring red syrup too.
It's more refreshing.

259
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:26,000
And you, just eat. Go ahead and dig in.

260
00:22:26,080 --> 00:22:27,560
This is all delicious food.

261
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:30,000
Eat up and make yourself at home.

262
00:22:30,080 --> 00:22:32,120
Alright? Enjoy your meal.

263
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:02,200
Please let me borrow it for now.

264
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:15,640
Again, huh?

265
00:23:15,720 --> 00:23:18,200
Phong, what's that woman
doing running around here?

266
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:22,440
Hey, isn't that Pinanong?

267
00:23:22,520 --> 00:23:24,200
- Follow her.
- Go, go.

268
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:34,800
Pin! Move! Get out of there!

269
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:37,200
Please let me go, Mr. Yai.

270
00:24:37,280 --> 00:24:38,720
Get out of there, Pin!

271
00:24:39,360 --> 00:24:40,720
Get out!

272
00:24:41,520 --> 00:24:42,960
Get out, Pin!

273
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:46,920
Hey, there aren't any workers

274
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:49,120
within the blast radius, correct?

275
00:24:49,200 --> 00:24:50,040
Yes, Boss.

276
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:53,840
Dad, can I take cover over there?

277
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:55,960
Look at you, Pan.

278
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:58,600
Want me to buy you a skirt?

279
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:04,680
Come on, Dad.

280
00:25:04,760 --> 00:25:07,040
I'm your legal advisor,

281
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:08,680
not an explosives expert like Yai.

282
00:25:09,320 --> 00:25:10,440
Really, Pan?

283
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:17,600
Hey, stop right here. Stop.

284
00:25:21,880 --> 00:25:22,840
Pin!

285
00:25:23,680 --> 00:25:26,200
What are you doing? Pin.

286
00:25:27,760 --> 00:25:29,080
- Let go.
- Come with me now.

287
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:31,840
Are you planning to kill me to silence me?

288
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:34,840
Damn, enough already. I won't lock you up.

289
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:36,720
In exchange,
you must never see Tatsana again.

290
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:38,720
But now you need to get out of here.

291
00:25:38,800 --> 00:25:42,520
No. I'd rather die than not see Mr. Na.

292
00:25:45,080 --> 00:25:46,240
Let go.

293
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:25,760
Mr. Yai.

294
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:28,600
Yai.

295
00:26:29,600 --> 00:26:30,680
What do we do, Dad?

296
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:40,080
On.

297
00:26:40,920 --> 00:26:42,560
Auntie transferred the money.

298
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:45,040
The trip is on as planned.

299
00:26:48,080 --> 00:26:50,040
I need to fly back home immediately.

300
00:26:50,120 --> 00:26:51,280
Dad is not doing well.

301
00:26:51,360 --> 00:26:54,440
Oh? Is it anything serious?

302
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:56,960
I don't know.

303
00:26:57,680 --> 00:27:00,920
But I suspect my credit card was suspended

304
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:02,360
because of this.

305
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:09,960
It'll be okay. I'm here for you.

306
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:13,760
I'll quickly check the flight again.

307
00:27:22,680 --> 00:27:24,360
Thank you.

308
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:26,800
I love you.

309
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:32,160
Ow, ow, Aunt Pen. It hurts.

310
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:33,440
It's nothing.

311
00:27:33,520 --> 00:27:35,280
- Be more gentle.
- It'll heal quickly.

312
00:27:38,120 --> 00:27:41,760
Should I kick you again, you weakling?

313
00:27:42,520 --> 00:27:44,920
Dad, I'm your son, not a soccer ball.

314
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:47,120
Stop kicking me all the time.

315
00:27:47,800 --> 00:27:49,520
You're always so harsh on your only son.

316
00:27:49,600 --> 00:27:53,560
Hey, I raised you myself.

317
00:27:53,640 --> 00:27:56,160
If I can't teach you to be a man…

318
00:27:57,320 --> 00:27:59,720
then you'll be a eunuch.

319
00:27:59,800 --> 00:28:00,960
Panthep.

320
00:28:01,520 --> 00:28:05,360
- Come here.
- Hey. Uh, go ahead then.

321
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:08,240
Your lineage will end with me here.

322
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:13,680
Enough already.
I don't know what's wrong with you guys.

323
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:15,840
Hey, I have something to ask you.

324
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:21,120
Aren't you curious what's the deal

325
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:23,520
with Mr. Yai and Pin?

326
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:25,080
Ugh, Aunt Pen.

327
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:26,600
Are you a bit too slow to catch on?

328
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:30,760
I could tell from the start
that Yai has always liked Pin,

329
00:28:30,840 --> 00:28:32,320
ever since they were kids.

330
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:34,000
Really?

331
00:28:34,080 --> 00:28:37,320
- Yeah.
- Why didn't you tell me?

332
00:28:37,400 --> 00:28:38,640
I thought you already knew.

333
00:28:38,720 --> 00:28:41,400
Every time,
you always keep things to yourself.

334
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:51,640
Call Aunt Pen over to do it for me.

335
00:28:56,840 --> 00:28:59,200
Aunt Pen is taking care of Mr. Pan.

336
00:29:00,160 --> 00:29:01,840
Just let me treat your wound.

337
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:04,840
If you leave it longer,
it will become more swollen.

338
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:08,520
Did you forget I'm a cutthroat

339
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:10,400
who was about to bury you alive?

340
00:29:11,840 --> 00:29:13,360
I'm sorry.

341
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:17,120
I didn't realize
that area was a stone mine.

342
00:29:45,440 --> 00:29:46,400
Hey.

343
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:50,560
Do you love him so much
that you would die for him?

344
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:04,240
Do you have someone you love, Mr. Yai?

345
00:30:07,440 --> 00:30:08,360
I don't.

346
00:30:11,440 --> 00:30:14,360
Maybe that's why you don't understand.

347
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:18,640
When you love someone,

348
00:30:19,520 --> 00:30:21,560
you're always thinking about them.

349
00:30:24,200 --> 00:30:26,200
"What are they doing now?"

350
00:30:27,440 --> 00:30:29,080
"Are they awake yet?"

351
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,280
"Have they eaten yet?"

352
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:35,480
"Are they happy?"

353
00:30:38,440 --> 00:30:41,760
They appear in your thoughts all the time.

354
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:46,960
And all those thoughts

355
00:30:48,240 --> 00:30:51,400
only hurt you more every day.

356
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:54,840
That's right.

357
00:30:57,360 --> 00:30:59,240
How do you know?

358
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:05,760
I remember people talking about it.

359
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:09,840
People like me just take who we want.

360
00:31:15,960 --> 00:31:17,240
Honestly,

361
00:31:18,320 --> 00:31:21,440
do you really think
Na will lower himself to marry you?

362
00:31:25,080 --> 00:31:26,720
Even though I'm lower than him,

363
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:31,280
Mr. Na has never been disgusted by me.

364
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:36,000
He's never treated me as just
a servant girl, unlike what you're doing.

365
00:31:37,240 --> 00:31:39,920
I just wanted to bring you
back to your senses.

366
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,440
But why?

367
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:44,920
Why should I stop dreaming about him

368
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:50,360
when it's a small happiness
that I can find?

369
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:53,360
If you want to help me,

370
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:57,040
just let me be
in my own silly little world.

371
00:31:58,120 --> 00:31:59,440
Can you?

372
00:32:29,680 --> 00:32:32,520
If you want to dream about him so much,
then do it all you want!

373
00:32:36,480 --> 00:32:40,000
Ugh, what nonsense are you yelling now?

374
00:32:40,080 --> 00:32:42,360
I thought you two
were already sweethearts.

375
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:45,120
Who would want to be sweet
with that Puny Pin?

376
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:46,960
She's so annoying.

377
00:32:50,080 --> 00:32:53,400
Well, then the big news
that my source sent

378
00:32:53,480 --> 00:32:54,880
probably doesn't need to be shared.

379
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:56,680
What news?

380
00:32:57,320 --> 00:32:59,640
About your rival in love, Na.

381
00:33:04,480 --> 00:33:06,080
ROSSAANG

382
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:08,120
Hey, is this…

383
00:33:08,200 --> 00:33:11,320
Does Pin know yet
that he has another life there?

384
00:33:14,800 --> 00:33:16,800
Are you considering a new plan?

385
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:19,520
Yes, Uncle.

386
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:27,680
Don't look at me, Dad.

387
00:33:28,280 --> 00:33:29,360
There.

388
00:33:29,440 --> 00:33:31,680
Talk to him yourself. I'm not involved.

389
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:33,160
I have my reasons, Uncle,

390
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:35,960
so that everything wraps up faster.

391
00:33:40,960 --> 00:33:41,880
Stand up.

392
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:48,400
Scold me however you want.

393
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:51,120
I'm tired of arguing with you.

394
00:33:53,840 --> 00:33:56,920
I'm tired of talking to you too.

395
00:33:57,760 --> 00:34:00,800
Fine, then we don't need to talk.

396
00:34:06,640 --> 00:34:09,040
If you don't want to talk, then don't.

397
00:34:09,120 --> 00:34:10,920
I'm going to take a shower and go to bed.

398
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:13,480
We'll be leaving early in the morning.

399
00:34:16,080 --> 00:34:17,440
Where will you be going?

400
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:22,880
Didn't you keep whining
about wanting to go home?

401
00:34:24,120 --> 00:34:26,840
You're taking me back to the farm?

402
00:34:28,159 --> 00:34:30,560
I knew you were messing with me,

403
00:34:31,159 --> 00:34:33,560
but you're actually a reasonable person.

404
00:34:34,719 --> 00:34:37,679
Thank you so much, Mr. Yai.

405
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:43,199
What do I get for being nice to you?

406
00:34:44,520 --> 00:34:45,679
What would you like me to do?

407
00:34:45,760 --> 00:34:46,840
Just tell me.

408
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:51,040
Are you sure you'll do it if I ask?

409
00:34:56,960 --> 00:35:01,480
Um… If I can, of course.

410
00:35:07,840 --> 00:35:09,480
Someday, I'll ask for…

411
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:15,040
Go ahead.

412
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:17,680
Go to sleep
and have sweet dreams about your darling.

413
00:35:18,240 --> 00:35:19,080
Go.

414
00:36:22,120 --> 00:36:23,480
Please wait a moment.

415
00:36:34,240 --> 00:36:35,960
You see what I'm holding?

416
00:36:36,040 --> 00:36:37,840
Prep the shards.

417
00:36:37,920 --> 00:36:39,160
I don't care how expensive it is.

418
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,120
See you.

419
00:36:44,560 --> 00:36:45,400
Nee.

420
00:36:46,640 --> 00:36:48,600
- Oh? Na?
- Hey.

421
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:52,680
Let me borrow 2,000.

422
00:36:52,760 --> 00:36:53,840
I need to pay for the taxi.

423
00:36:55,640 --> 00:36:56,880
What?

424
00:36:56,960 --> 00:36:58,960
- You arrive and rob me right away.
- Thank you.

425
00:36:59,040 --> 00:37:02,480
Why is the international grad so cheap?

426
00:37:03,160 --> 00:37:05,040
I used all my money for the plane tickets.

427
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:08,000
And why is the house so quiet?

428
00:37:08,520 --> 00:37:09,400
Where's Auntie?

429
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:13,880
She went out with her not-just-friend
last night and still hasn't come back.

430
00:37:14,960 --> 00:37:17,240
Not-just-friend? What's that?

431
00:37:18,200 --> 00:37:22,000
Not-just-friend
is a special kind of friend.

432
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:24,200
Special friend.

433
00:37:24,880 --> 00:37:26,240
I told you that

434
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:29,520
once we got rid of that bad luck,
my luck would skyrocket.

435
00:37:30,920 --> 00:37:31,760
That's right.

436
00:37:31,840 --> 00:37:34,080
You were on a roll last night.

437
00:37:35,560 --> 00:37:37,040
Oh. Na?

438
00:37:41,640 --> 00:37:43,480
When did you arrive?

439
00:37:46,720 --> 00:37:49,120
Why didn't you call me first
so I could pick you up?

440
00:37:49,720 --> 00:37:52,920
Oh, I called, but you didn't pick up.

441
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:55,200
She was probably having fun.

442
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:58,600
Madam went to a birthday party in Bangkok.

443
00:38:00,360 --> 00:38:03,480
This is Teera, the farm manager.

444
00:38:03,560 --> 00:38:05,280
He's been a great help running the farm.

445
00:38:05,880 --> 00:38:08,040
Maybe not only a great help on the farm…

446
00:38:09,640 --> 00:38:11,720
but also great somewhere else too.

447
00:38:13,120 --> 00:38:16,240
Nee, shut your mouth.

448
00:38:22,520 --> 00:38:26,840
It's only been a few years,
and yet you look so handsome and radiant.

449
00:38:26,920 --> 00:38:28,960
Give me a hug to make up for missing you.

450
00:38:35,520 --> 00:38:38,440
What? Mr. Yai came back?

451
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:42,520
And why didn't you tell me?

452
00:38:42,600 --> 00:38:44,320
Don't be so shocked.

453
00:38:44,400 --> 00:38:48,000
After all,
you're still the only heir here.

454
00:38:48,680 --> 00:38:52,040
Yai did come back, but he went
and robbed a gambling den downtown,

455
00:38:52,120 --> 00:38:55,000
so the thugs hunted him down,
and he ran away.

456
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:56,440
Robbed a gambling den?

457
00:38:58,120 --> 00:38:59,720
Has Mr. Yai turned into a thief?

458
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:02,000
Nowadays,

459
00:39:02,080 --> 00:39:05,160
he's much more vile and cruel than before.

460
00:39:05,240 --> 00:39:07,240
I didn't want you to return

461
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:10,280
because I was afraid you'd run into him.

462
00:39:10,360 --> 00:39:14,440
Luckily, he doesn't have
as much merit as you,

463
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:16,040
so he brought ruin upon himself.

464
00:39:18,120 --> 00:39:19,600
That's good.

465
00:39:19,680 --> 00:39:22,120
If I had brought On here
while Mr. Yai was around,

466
00:39:22,200 --> 00:39:24,640
things would definitely be messy.

467
00:39:25,480 --> 00:39:26,440
On?

468
00:39:27,560 --> 00:39:30,200
Oh. Onsa-ang,

469
00:39:30,280 --> 00:39:31,960
the daughter
of the former deputy minister?

470
00:39:32,560 --> 00:39:36,760
Yes. She's incredibly refined.

471
00:39:36,840 --> 00:39:38,600
She wouldn't be able to take it.

472
00:39:39,360 --> 00:39:41,000
No need to worry anymore.

473
00:39:41,080 --> 00:39:44,040
You're now the only heir to Paisal Farm

474
00:39:44,120 --> 00:39:46,680
which is worth hundreds of millions.

475
00:39:46,760 --> 00:39:49,640
Any woman
would fall head over heels for you.

476
00:39:51,280 --> 00:39:54,120
So… do you like the room?

477
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:58,280
I renovated it specifically
just to welcome you back.

478
00:39:58,360 --> 00:39:59,280
Do you like it?

479
00:40:11,840 --> 00:40:13,760
This is definitely Pinanong's work.

480
00:40:15,760 --> 00:40:20,040
Oh, and where are Pin and Aunt Un?

481
00:40:20,840 --> 00:40:21,800
I didn't see them around.

482
00:41:08,440 --> 00:41:11,600
Alright. I called everyone here today

483
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:14,360
because I have some good news to share.

484
00:41:15,080 --> 00:41:16,120
Oh?

485
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:17,720
Are we getting a bonus, Manager?

486
00:41:18,840 --> 00:41:20,400
Bonus! Bonus! Bonus!

487
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:22,040
Pipe down. Listen up.

488
00:41:22,720 --> 00:41:25,960
There will definitely be a bonus,
because now,

489
00:41:26,040 --> 00:41:27,800
the real farm owner is back.

490
00:41:31,360 --> 00:41:33,080
Give it up for Mr. Tatsana.

491
00:41:40,160 --> 00:41:43,520
This is Tatsana, my nephew.

492
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:47,320
He just completed his master's degree
in business administration in Australia.

493
00:41:48,560 --> 00:41:50,280
From now on,

494
00:41:50,360 --> 00:41:53,960
he'll be managing
Paisal Farm and Resort on my behalf.

495
00:41:54,040 --> 00:41:55,680
Woo!

496
00:41:58,400 --> 00:42:02,760
Yeah, I plan to improve our organization

497
00:42:02,840 --> 00:42:04,680
using the 6Ps system

498
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:09,600
and develop our resources
to increase our farm's value.

499
00:42:09,680 --> 00:42:12,880
I hope to receive everyone's cooperation.

500
00:42:14,040 --> 00:42:15,280
Very well said.

501
00:42:15,880 --> 00:42:17,160
Excuse me.

502
00:42:18,720 --> 00:42:19,800
What about Mr. Yai?

503
00:42:20,960 --> 00:42:22,880
He is a robber and murderer,

504
00:42:22,960 --> 00:42:24,960
and he was using this place as a hideout.

505
00:42:25,760 --> 00:42:30,120
When he learned
the police were onto him, he fled.

506
00:42:31,320 --> 00:42:34,560
Then Pin might be missing
because she was kidnapped by Mr. Yai.

507
00:42:35,880 --> 00:42:38,480
Guys, we need to tell the police
so they can apprehend Mr. Yai.

508
00:42:38,560 --> 00:42:39,720
No.

509
00:42:47,640 --> 00:42:48,520
She's right.

510
00:42:49,160 --> 00:42:50,480
If it becomes a big story,

511
00:42:51,120 --> 00:42:52,640
our farm's reputation will be
negatively affected.

512
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:54,000
It's not worth it.

513
00:42:54,080 --> 00:42:56,840
But someone's gone missing.

514
00:42:56,920 --> 00:42:58,800
Aren't we going to do anything?

515
00:42:58,880 --> 00:43:00,440
Isn't that a bit too cold-blooded?

516
00:43:00,520 --> 00:43:01,560
Jom.

517
00:43:07,120 --> 00:43:10,280
Uh, what he's trying to say
is that we have a lot of people.

518
00:43:10,360 --> 00:43:12,800
We should be able to help find Pin.

519
00:43:14,040 --> 00:43:17,520
Well, I agree with him, Auntie.

520
00:43:18,600 --> 00:43:19,680
Guys, let's go.

521
00:43:20,280 --> 00:43:22,560
Anyone who wants to
can go look for Pinanong.

522
00:43:22,640 --> 00:43:25,600
But I'll hire new workers
to do those jobs in your places.

523
00:43:26,520 --> 00:43:27,360
Fine!

524
00:43:27,960 --> 00:43:30,640
I don't want to work
for a heartless employer like this!

525
00:43:31,520 --> 00:43:32,360
Hey.

526
00:43:32,440 --> 00:43:34,640
Jom, who are you calling heartless?

527
00:43:34,720 --> 00:43:35,960
And what are you gonna do?

528
00:43:36,040 --> 00:43:37,240
- What do you want?
- Hey!

529
00:43:37,320 --> 00:43:38,480
- Hey, Jom.
- What's with you?

530
00:43:41,800 --> 00:43:43,640
- Go apologize to Madam.
- No!

531
00:43:49,120 --> 00:43:51,760
Jom. Jom!

532
00:43:53,760 --> 00:43:55,440
Jom!

533
00:43:57,600 --> 00:44:00,360
Whoever doesn't want to stay, leave now.

534
00:44:00,440 --> 00:44:03,200
I don't want to keep any thugs around,

535
00:44:03,280 --> 00:44:05,720
especially Mr. Yai's underlings.

536
00:44:06,240 --> 00:44:07,320
Remember.

537
00:44:07,400 --> 00:44:13,160
From now on, the sole owner
of Paisal Farm is Mr. Tatsana!

538
00:44:21,680 --> 00:44:23,120
Super cool.

539
00:44:29,200 --> 00:44:33,680
In that case, I'll be at your service too,

540
00:44:33,760 --> 00:44:34,600
Mr. Tatsana.

541
00:44:57,480 --> 00:45:00,320
<i>Let's settle all debts</i>
<i>and their interest today.</i>

542
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:03,000
If you're going to kill me, go ahead.

543
00:45:03,080 --> 00:45:05,320
I will take control of all operations.

544
00:45:06,480 --> 00:45:10,480
And here is the list
of the employees' new positions.

545
00:45:10,560 --> 00:45:12,520
I think Mr. Na should work in the office.

546
00:45:12,600 --> 00:45:15,120
I want him to learn
from the lower levels up,

547
00:45:15,200 --> 00:45:19,400
<i>so people won't gossip that he's soft</i>

548
00:45:19,480 --> 00:45:21,320
<i>and can't even handle low-level jobs.</i>

549
00:46:01,080 --> 00:46:03,360
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
